1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,530
Ideas are fruits of your thinking, but they've got to be harnessed and put to work to have value.

2
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:13,171
Each year, an oak tree produces enough acorns to populate a good-sized forest.

3
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:19,251
Yet, from these bushels of seeds, perhaps only one or two acorns will become a tree.

4
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:27,891
The squirrels destroy most of them, and the hard ground beneath the tree doesn't give the few remaining seeds much chance for a start.

5
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,131
So it is with ideas.

6
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:32,131
Very few bear fruit.

7
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,530
Ideas are highly perishable.

8
00:00:34,641 --> 00:00:40,291
If we're not on guard, the squirrels, negative-thinking people, will destroy most of them.

9
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:49,171
Ideas require special handling from the time they are born until they're transformed into practical ways for doing things better.

10
00:00:49,601 --> 00:00:53,811
Use these three ways to harness and develop your ideas.

11
00:00:53,811 --> 00:00:55,251
1.

12
00:00:55,601 --> 00:00:57,490
Don't let ideas escape.

13
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:58,691
Write them down.

14
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:05,811
Every day lots of good ideas are born only to die quickly because they aren't nailed to paper.

15
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:11,490
Memory is a weak slave when it comes to preserving and nurturing brand new ideas.

16
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:14,771
Carry a notebook or some small cards with you.

17
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:17,251
When you get an idea, write it down.

18
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:25,171
A friend who travels a lot keeps a clipboard beside him so that he can write down an idea the instant it occurs to him.

19
00:01:25,601 --> 00:01:31,891
People with fertile creative minds know a good idea may sprout any time, any place.

20
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:36,930
Don't let ideas escape, else you destroy the fruits of your thinking.

21
00:01:37,041 --> 00:01:38,291
Fence them in.

22
00:01:38,291 --> 00:01:39,811
2.

23
00:01:40,081 --> 00:01:42,450
Next, review your ideas.

24
00:01:42,561 --> 00:01:45,331
File these ideas in an active file.

25
00:01:45,601 --> 00:01:49,490
The file can be an elaborate cabinet, or it can be a desk drawer.

26
00:01:49,601 --> 00:01:51,251
A shoebox will do.

27
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:56,131
But build a file, and then examine your storehouse of ideas regularly.

28
00:01:56,400 --> 00:02:01,891
As you go over your ideas, some may, for very good reasons, have no value at all.

29
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,091
Get rid of them.

30
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:06,930
But so long as the idea has any promise, keep it.

31
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:08,771
3.

32
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:11,891
Cultivate and fertilize your idea.

33
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,211
Now make your idea grow.

34
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,251
Think about it.

35
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:18,050
Tie the idea to related ideas.

36
00:02:18,641 --> 00:02:23,251
Read anything you can find that is in any way akin to your idea.

37
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:25,331
Investigate all angles.

38
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:31,010
Then, when the time is ripe, put it to work for yourself, your job, your future.

